The paper deals with optimization of a communication network with random channel connectivity, which is a common problem in the field of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of Markov decision processes (MDP) and optimization algorithms suggests a focus on control and optimization (cs.SY, cs.MA). The paper also deals with the specific problem of relay buffering, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC).
